### Create an Organization Quota

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/organization_quotas" \
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
  -H "Content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
        "name": "production"
      }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 201 Created
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :single_organization_quota %>
```


This endpoint creates a new organization quota, but does not assign it to a specific organization.

To create an organization quota you must be an admin.

#### Definition
`POST /v3/organization_quotas`

#### Required parameters

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | -----------
**name** | _string_ | Name of the quota.

#### Optional parameters
Name | Type | Description | Default |
---- | ---- | ----------- | ------- |
 **apps.per_process_memory_in_mb** | _integer_ | Maximum memory a single process or task can use. | null (infinite) |
| **apps.total_instances** | _integer_ | Total instances all the started processes in an organization can have. | null (infinite) |
| **apps.per_app_tasks** | _integer_ | Maximum number of running tasks a single application can have. | null (infinite) |
| **services.paid_services_allowed** | _boolean_ | If instances of paid service plans can be created. | true |
| **services.total_service_instances** | _integer_ | Total number of service instances that an organization can have. | null (infinite) |
| **services.total_service_keys** | _integer_ | Total number of service keys that an organization can have. | null (infinite) |
| **routes.total_routes** | _integer_ | Total number of routes that an organization can have. | null (infinite) |
| **routes.total_reserved_ports** | _integer_ | Total number of ports that all routes in an organization can reserve. | null (infinite) |
| **relationships.organizations** | [_to-many relationship_](#to-many-relationships) | A relationship to the organizations the quota applies to. | null (infinite) |

#### Permitted roles

Role | Notes
--- | ---
Admin |
